    <h2 class="internal">About me</h2>
    <h3>head</h3>

    <p>I've always been fascinated by computers: my very first love was a Commodore 64. I wasn't really a Basic
      programmer badass but, who cares, I had a lot of fun with it.</p>

    <p>In 2000 I started working as a web designer for a small web agency in Merano (the town in Northern Italy where I
      was born). I quickly realized this was the job I wanted to do but, in a city like mine, it would not be easy.
      For this reason, the following year, I decided to move to Milan. <br>Honestly, it was not easy even in Milan, especially in the early years.</p>

    <p>After a couple of years, the web began to change a lot. Those where the years when tableless layouts came out and in which most people wasn't able to
      understand why using CSS for the presentation was way better that using markup.
      <br>The turning point for me was the enlightening <a
        href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Designing_with_Web_Standards">Designing with web Standards</a> by Jeffrey Zeldman. <br>Reading this book
      made me passionate about writing (clean) code, so I decided to quit the "graphic" part of my job and to dedicate all my efforts to the code.</p>

    <p>I'm specialized in cutting-edge, standard compliant website developing, for both desktop and mobile with wide experience in high
      traffic optimization. My technical skills include HTML, CSS and Javascript developing. I have experience
      in team leading as well.</p>

    <p>Not only am I passionate about writing code, but also in getting the things done smoothly, taking advantage of the fantastic tools we have today
      .<br>Do Gulp, Bower and Yeoman sound familiar to you?</p>

    <p>The experience gained over the years allowed me to work and to coordinate teams for clients such as
      Corriere della Sera, Gazzetta dello Sport, Unicredit, Tradinglab, Lavazza, Donna Moderna (Mondadori), RAS and
      others.</p>

    <p>After lots of years working for web agencies and as free-lance, I was looking for something different and more challenging that would allow me to reach the turning point in my professional career. At the time I'm working for
        <a href="http://gild.com">Gild</a></p>

    <p>In 2013 I founded <a href="http://milanojs.com">Milano JS</a>, the first Javascript User Group in Milan.</p>

    <p>Due to my technical expertise and my influence in the developers community, Google selected me to be one of the members of the
      <strong>Web Technologies Google Developers Expert</strong> with the specialization on Polymer.</p>

    <p>If you want to learn more about my professional profile, please visit my <a
        href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/granze">Linkedin page</a></p>
